    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-11-16T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-11-16T05:00:00-05:00" n="480"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">365.115/4: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-16T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 16, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 16—8:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>335. Department’s telegram No. 112, November 15, 7 p.m. It is understood that all
                    Stock Exchange privileges in Italy formerly held by persons of the Jewish race
                    have been withdrawn without distinction of nationality.</p>
                <pb facs="0610" n="602" xml:id="pg_602"/>
                <p>On October 19 the Embassy addressed a communication to the Foreign Office
                    pointing out that the responsibilities of Mr. Blattner’s position as the
                    representative of an American concern were such that withdrawal of these
                    privileges would operate to the detriment of the company’s interests and
                    requesting that the special commission afford sympathetic consideration to his
                    case.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
